pl.edu.icm.cermine.structure.model

Class BxObject<C,T,P>

  • java.lang.Object
    • pl.edu.icm.cermine.structure.model.BxObject<C,T,P>
  • Type Parameters:
    C - child type
    T - the actual type
    P - parent type (e.g. BxPage for BxZone)
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Iterable<C>, Indexable<T>, Printable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    BxChunk, BxDocument, BxLine, BxPage, BxWord, BxZone, BxZoneGroup

    public abstract class BxObject<C,T,P>
extends Object
implements Indexable<T>, Iterable<C>, Printable, Serializable
    Common class for all Bx* classes having physical properties (this is to say BxBounds).
    Author:
    Dominika Tkaczyk (d.tkaczyk@icm.edu.pl), Pawel Szostek
    See Also:
    Serialized Form
